steps.instruction:
For a more step-by-step guide go [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2016/09/01/inside-out-pumpkin-muffins-bakealong)

### Prep
- Preheat the oven to 400°F
- Line a standard 12-cup muffin pan with muffin papers, and grease the papers

### Making the Streusel (Topping)
1. Whisk together the flour, sugar, oats, and salt
2. Work in the butter, mixing until coarse crumbs form
3. Set the topping aside

### Making the Filling
1. Make sure the cream cheese is at room temperature
    - If it's not, place it in a microwave-safe bowl, and heat on low power for 40 seconds, just to soften it
2. Stir in the sugar and vanilla or Fiori di Sicilia, if using

### Making the Batter
1. Whisk together the pumpkin, eggs, brown sugar, oil, boiled cider, salt, spices, baking powder, baking soda, and milk
2. Scrape down the sides and bottom of the bowl
3. Add the flour and mix until well combined
4. Scrape down the sides and bottom of the bowl and beat briefly to incorporate the scrapings
5. Drop a scant 2 tablespoons of the batter (a heaping tablespoon cookie scoop works well here) into each muffin cup, spreading it to cover the bottom
6. Dollop on a heaping tablespoon of filling, then cover with another 2 tablespoons of batter
7. Sprinkle each muffin with some of the streusel topping
8. Bake the muffins for 18 to 20 minutes, until a cake tester inserted towards the edge (not into the filling) comes out crumb-free
9. Remove the muffins from the oven
10. As soon as they're cool enough to safely handle, transfer them to a rack to cool completely
11. Enjoy fresh-baked muffins within 2 to 3 hours; refrigerate up to 3 days for longer storage. Freeze, well-wrapped, up to 3 weeks. Rewarm cold muffins in a preheated 350°F oven, tented with foil. Or heat briefly in a microwave set at low power

#### Tips
- Boiled cider isn't something you can easily make yourself, simply by boiling cider. But it's so wonderful, in so many different fruit desserts (especially ones with apples), it's worth it to keep a bottle on hand. It'll last for months in the fridge
- Want to make this recipe dairy-free? Use non-dairy milk in the batter; coconut oil or margarine in the topping, and vegan (non-dairy) cream cheese in the filling
- This recipe will make 24 mini muffins; bake minis in a preheated 375°F oven for 12 to 15 minutes

ingredients.note: Boiled Cider for best flavor, can also substitute in honey
Or 1 tsp cinnamon, 1/4 tsp cloves, 1/4 ginger
Optional. You can also use Fiori di Sicilia
